44060|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同时，她的作品也曾在各大报纸和艺术评论中出现 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Immersive Glass Portals Unveil the Secret Life of Nature|url=https://www.vice.com/en/article/9anxw5/immersive-glass-portals-vuela-vuela|access-date=2020-10-08|website=www.vice.com|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023065311/https://www.vice.com/en/article/9anxw5/immersive-glass-portals-vuela-vuela|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyond Two Dimensions: Add New Media To Your Collection With These Innovative Works|url=http://www.artspace.com/magazine/interviews_features/beyond-two-dimensions-add-new-media-to-your-collection-with-these-innovative-works|access-date=2020-10-08|website=Artspace|language=en|archive-date=2021-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210403161157/https://www.artspace.com/magazine/interviews_features/expert_eye/beyond-two-dimensions-add-new-media-to-your-collection-with-these-innovative-works-56630|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2019-06-16|title=View to a Thrill: a bumper summer harvest in store|page=Newspaper - City & Life - Art|work=[[South_China_Morning_Post|South China Morning Post]]|url=https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5434a90fe4b0ebb220d295ea/1574119342666-V2KLSGKG88IH6PE6M3F4/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kOpZ97w90Hyfo-amyhntOe97gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QHyNOqBUUEtDDsRWrJLTmMCg6RGY8TrcVSOIk4QoDPuWlIueN4Z1Oj_tiTdKfNx8Eicb_lVEXvs4KcMHeOhLD/HK+Press+.jpg?format=500w|access-date=2020-10-09|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108122027/https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5434a90fe4b0ebb220d295ea/1574119342666-V2KLSGKG88IH6PE6M3F4/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kOpZ97w90Hyfo-amyhntOe97gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z5QHyNOqBUUEtDDsRWrJLTmMCg6RGY8TrcVSOIk4QoDPuWlIueN4Z1Oj_tiTdKfNx8Eicb_lVEXvs4KcMHeOhLD/HK+Press+.jpg?format=500w|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=KASE|first=LORI MILLER|title=Toddlers, Even Babies At New Britain Museum: Never Too Early To Start Art Education|url=https://www.courant.com/hartford-magazine/hc-hm-museum-education-start-early-20160225-story.html|access-date=2020-10-08|website=courant.com|archive-date=2016-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227132207/http://www.courant.com/hartford-magazine/hc-hm-museum-education-start-early-20160225-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Diciembre 2016|first=Por: Joaquín Badajoz 14 de|title=Katja Loher o la armonía de las esferas|url=https://eldiariony.com/2016/12/14/katja-loher-o-la-armonia-de-las-esferas/|access-date=2020-10-08|website=El Diario NY|language=es|archive-date=2021-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210403161149/https://eldiariony.com/2016/12/14/katja-loher-o-la-armonia-de-las-esferas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。安德烈·薩爾曼出版的多套丛书都有介绍<ref>{{Cite web|title=Results for 'au:Katja Loher' [WorldCat.org]|url=https://www.worldcat.org/search?q=au:Katja+Loher&qt=advanced&dblist=638|access-date=2020-10-06|website=www.worldcat.org|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021013043/https://www.worldcat.org/search?q=au:Katja+Loher&qt=advanced&dblist=638|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 艺术作品 ==
[[檔案:Beebubble,_glass_artwork_by_Katja_Loher.jpg|thumb]]
洛涵近期的艺术作品主要有：《{{lang|en|Bubbles}}》, 在2010年苏黎世安德烈·薩爾曼畫廊首次亮相 。该装置以肥皂泡状玻璃碎片为基础，3D视频在内部投影配合上方舞者轻快舞蹈的录影，创作灵感来源于智利诗人[[巴勃羅·聶魯達|巴勃羅·聶魯達]]的诗作<ref>{{Cite web|title=Katja Loher|url=https://www.artlog.net/de/kunstbulletin-5-2013/katja-loher|access-date=2020-10-05|website=www.artlog.net|language=de|archive-date=2021-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210403161157/https://www.artlog.net/de/kunstbulletin-5-2013/katja-loher|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《{{lang|en|Time Bubble}}》於2012年在纽约首次亮相，以美国作曲家兼钢琴家[[菲利普·葛拉斯|菲利普·葛拉斯]]为原型，结合时间元素创造的艺术作品。该雕塑运用多种装置创作出了如同管弦乐队演奏般的意境 <ref>{{Cite web|date=2015-12-01|title=Katja Loher's Interplanetary Orchestration in New York|url=http://www.drosteeffectmag.com/katja-loher-interplanetary-orchestration-in-new-york/|access-date=2020-10-08|website=Droste Effect Mag|archive-date=2016-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160430195400/http://www.drosteeffectmag.com/katja-loher-interplanetary-orchestration-in-new-york/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。《{{lang|en|Bang Bang}}》於2014年在纽约C24畫廊展出，从顶部欣賞此装置艺术品会看到有如{{Link-en|巴士比·柏克萊|Busby Berkeley}}式舞蹈演员曼妙身姿的投影影像，不僅具有幽默感，也令人思索抽象的存在性問題<ref>{{Cite web|title=Katja Loher Expresses The Fragmentation Of Her Beloved Harmonious Cosmos|url=https://www.artlyst.com/reviews/katja-loher-expresses-the-fragmentation-of-her-beloved-harmonious-cosmos/|access-date=2020-10-05|website=Artlyst|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210403161055/https://www.artlyst.com/reviews/katja-loher-expresses-the-fragmentation-of-her-beloved-harmonious-cosmos/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。同时在C24畫廊展出的还有《{{lang|en|Videoplanet-Orchestra}}》，这件作品同样是艺术投影结合装置艺术，配以音乐，显示了人与人、人与自然、人与科技之间的关系<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mohr|first=Claire Kovacs, Melissa|title='The Gallery Gap' Ep. 7: Earth Day Edition|url=https://www.wvik.org/post/gallery-gap-ep-7-earth-day-edition|access-date=2020-09-19|website=www.wvik.org|language=en|archive-date=2017-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924220543/http://wvik.org/post/gallery-gap-ep-7-earth-day-edition|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=GalleryLOG|title=Katja Loher at VOLTA NY 2014|date=2014-02-27|url=https://vimeo.com/87823375|access-date=2020-09-20|archive-date=2015-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123134244/https://vimeo.com/87823375|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
[[File:Videoplanets_by_Kaja_Loher.jpg|thumb]]
2015年在乔治亚州[[薩凡納|薩凡納]]展出的《{{lang|en|Beeplanet}}》通过对玻璃以及其他装置的运用显示了卡蒂雅对环境问题的担忧和关心。她运用蜜蜂这些小而敏感的生物，体现出我们生态系统中关键的一环。蜜蜂具有母系社会结构，并且通过舞蹈进行交流。所有这些生物与人类放在一起并有组织地游戏，强调了它们与我们平等的重要性<ref name=":102">{{Cite web|last=Chandler|first=Anna|title=PULSE Festival: Katja Loher|url=https://www.connectsavannah.com/savannah/pulse-festival-katja-loher/Content?oid=2518907|access-date=2021-01-05|website=Connect Savannah|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201014094120/https://www.connectsavannah.com/savannah/pulse-festival-katja-loher/Content?oid=2518907|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年，她回归纽约，作品《{{lang|es|Vuela Vuela}}》在C24畫廊继续展出。晶莹剔透的玻璃装置配以其他生物的投影，让观众感知到地球这个作为我们赖以生存的星球的美好<ref name=":11">{{Cite web|title=Vuela Vuela|url=https://www.c24gallery.com/vuela-vuela|access-date=2020-09-19|website=c24gallery.com|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229011938/https://www.c24gallery.com/vuela-vuela|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年，作品《{{lang|en|Where Does the Rainbow End?}}》獲瑞士電網公司總部永久珍藏。該作中的视频影像包括水、土、火和空气，随着时间线的移动渐渐进入“梦境”。观众在观看的同时不仅能体会到作品背后的哲学寓意，也对环境的日益恶化有所了解<ref>{{Cite web|title=Art and architecture|url=https://www.swissgrid.ch/en/home/about-us/company/art-and-architecture.html|access-date=2020-10-05|website=www.swissgrid.ch|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116095443/https://www.swissgrid.ch/en/home/about-us/company/art-and-architecture.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2019年，《{{lang|en|Seeds of Life}}》在香港、成都、北京和上海相继展出。在此过程中，卡蒂雅和中国水墨大师吴浩的合作給予她很深的啟發，中国水墨也在此系列作品中留下深刻印记。另外，中国传统的“五行”概念也在这一系列中有所体现<ref name=":02">{{Cite web|title=The House Collective's art programme with Swiss artist Katja Loher concludes at The Temple House|url=https://www.buro247.sg/culture/art-and-design/the-house-collective-debut-art-programme-with-swiss-artist-katja-loher-concludes-at-the-temple-house-in-chengdu-china.html|access-date=2020-09-17|website=BURO.|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922131749/https://www.buro247.sg/culture/art-and-design/the-house-collective-debut-art-programme-with-swiss-artist-katja-loher-concludes-at-the-temple-house-in-chengdu-china.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=@NatGeoUK|date=2019-05-20|title=A city guide to the cooler side of Beijing|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/travel/2019/05/city-guide-cooler-side-beijing|access-date=2020-09-20|website=National Geographic|language=en-gb|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205150322/https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/travel/2019/05/city-guide-cooler-side-beijing|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《{{lang|en|What Happens to the Swallows Who Are Late for Spring?}}》於2020年在安雅·蒂希畫廊展出。五彩斑斓的投影在看似鸟巢形状的玻璃球体上，展示了一个充满不同风情的宇宙生命。此装置艺术品旨在唤起人类对自己在宇宙中地位的批判性思考<ref name=":123" />。

